<item>
            <title>[FELIX-1504] ComponentInstance implementation is reused accross reactivations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-1504</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to the specification of the ComponentInstance interface, instances of this interface must not be reused after a component instance has been deactivated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, the ComponentInstance interface is implemented by the AbstractComponentManager class and thus is not replaced after the reactivation of a component.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The implementation of the ComponentInstance interface has to be refactored to reflect the life cycle of the actual component object (the object returned from ComponentInstance.getInstance().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
